e prayer rituals of any particular sect; it's about providing special concessions to one group (whoever they may be), while the same concessions are denied to everyone else, for no valid reason that I can determine. &#10;Aside from the fact that this particular group's rituals include gender segregation which violates the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms - the same rules should apply across the board, to all, and it seems they don't. &#10;Is this group paying rent for the space they demand several times a day? That levels the playing field, opening up the same opportunity for anyone else to do the same. Logistically that could be a nightmare for administrators (should everyone make the same demands) - but at least the ground rules are consistent and apply to all. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1076" language="en" documentId="1253" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="canajunlady" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1253" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="231"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="232" end="519"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="520" end="744"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="745" end="1076"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>